Now to what's coming next. Rule-driven applicability — the rule engine is the platform's next core capability. Instead of manual mapping, a control applies when an application meets defined conditions.
Take this example. The rule says: customer-facing applications classified as SOX automatically require Multi-Factor Authentication and audit-event evidence. The platform evaluates the rule against every application, every cycle.
The inputs come from source systems — LeanIX gives the platform hosting type, criticality, customer-facing, SOX classification, and more. The rule engine reads those attributes and produces the right set of controls.
The Risk Manager reviews exceptions, not every row. Auditable, not asserted. Rules become the unit of governance — not records.
